    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-11-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-11-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="145"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d145">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_RFD1">Roosevelt</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">President</gloss> to the Ambassador in
                        Turkey</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SLA1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Steinhardt</hi>
                    </persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d145fn1">Sent to the White House, apparently via
                        military channels; forwarded to the Department of State; and forwarded
                        further by the Department, in paraphrase, in telegram 902, November 20,
                        1943, 4 p.m., to the Legation at Ankara, marked “Most Secret and Personal”
                        and “U. S. Urgent”.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tunis</hi>
                        </placeName>] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-11-20">20 November
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>From the President to Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_SLA1"
                        >Steinhardt</persName>
                </p>
                <p>Hope you can come to Cairo either immediately or later. I hope to be there until
                    Saturday November 27 and to be back there about six days later.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
